fullName.value: HLA class II histocompatibility antigen, DO alpha chain

texts.value: Important modulator in the HLA class II restricted antigen presentation pathway by interaction with the HLA-DM molecule in B-cells. Modifies peptide exchange activity of HLA-DM
Heterodimer of an alpha chain (DOA) and a beta chain (DOB). Forms a heterotetrameric complex with an HLA-DM molecule during intracellular transport in endosomal/lysosomal compartments in B-cells
Complexes with HLA-DM molecule during intracellular transport and in endosomal/lysosomal compartments. Heterotetramerization is necessary to exit the ER
The following alleles of DOA are known: DOA*01:01, DOA*01:02 and DOA*01:03. The sequence shown is that of DOA*01:01
Belongs to the MHC class II family
